# ML Skill - Quick Start Guide

## Installation

```bash
# Install required dependencies
pip install mlflow optuna scikit-learn tensorflow torch
npm install -g optuna-dashboard
```

## Quick Usage

### 1. Experiment Tracking
```bash
cd examples
python experiment-tracking.py

# View results
mlflow ui
# Navigate to: http://localhost:5000
```

### 2. Hyperparameter Optimization
```bash
cd examples
node hyperparameter-optimization.js

# View visualizations in generated HTML files
```

### 3. Full MLOps Pipeline
```bash
cd examples
python mlops-pipeline.py
```

## Testing

```bash
# Python tests
cd tests
python -m pytest test-experiment-tracking.py -v
python -m pytest test-mlops-pipeline.py -v

# JavaScript tests
node test-hyperparameter-tuning.js
```

## Configuration

Edit templates in `resources/templates/`:
- `experiment-config.yaml` - Experiment settings
- `hyperparameter-space.json` - Search space
- `model-card.md` - Model documentation

## Scripts

Run production scripts from `resources/scripts/`:
- `python experiment-tracker.py --config <path>`
- `node hyperparameter-tuner.js --space <path> --trials 100`
- `bash model-registry.sh register <name> <version> <path>`
- `python ml-ops.py --pipeline full --model-name <name>`
